     <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-09-02 -->
	 
	 Geek Dinner with Jon Udell: Thursday, January 18, 7pm, Bellevue Crossroads Mall
	 </font>
     </h2>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><p align="center"><font color="#800040"><font face="Arial" size="6"><strong>This event is cancelled.<br /></strong></font><br /><font size="4"><strong>There&rsquo;s a </strong></font></font><a href="http://podcasting.meetup.com/22/calendar/5310365/"><font color="#800040" size="4"><strong>Seattle Podcasting Network Meetup</strong></font></a><font color="#800040"><font size="4"><strong> at the same time and this is a far better venue to hobnob with Jon Udell and local-area podcasters and luminaries.<br /></strong></font><br /><strong>For other Geek Dinner possibilities with Jon, </strong></font><a href="http://blog.jonudell.net/"><font color="#800040"><strong>check his blog</strong></font></a><font color="#800040"><strong>.</strong></font></p><hr><p><a href="http://blog.jonudell.net/">Jon Udell</a> is at Microsoft&rsquo;s Redmond Campus for the week of January 15.&nbsp; He&rsquo;s beginning&nbsp;<a href="http://weblog.infoworld.com/udell/2006/12/08.html">his new job</a> with <a href="http://www.jeffsandquist.com/PermaLink,guid,efaa07bd-1b4c-4002-912c-13edf8c1933a.aspx">Jeff Sandquist</a> and the <a href="http://channel9.msdn.com/">Channel 9</a>/<a href="http://on10.net/">on10</a> technology-evangelism folk.</p><p align="center">{tag: <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Jon+Udell" rel="tag">Jon Udell</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Geek+Dinner" rel="tag">Geek Dinner</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Bellevue" rel="tag">Bellevue</a>&nbsp;<a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Jeff+Sandquist" rel="tag">Jeff Sandquist</a>}</p><p>There will be an open Geek Dinner (you invite yourself) at the <a href="http://www.crossroadsbellevue.com/">Bellevue Crossroads Mall</a>, &nbsp;7 pm Thursday, January 18.&nbsp; There&rsquo;s a food court for your own preferences and tables and chairs down the central hall.&nbsp; Look for people with geek kits (laptops, too many electronic devices, etc.)&nbsp;who&rsquo;ve self-organized themselves into a discussion and dinner group.&nbsp;We&rsquo;ll also be looking for spots not too close to <a href="http://www.crossroadsbellevue.com/musicandevents/music.htm">the musical entertainment</a>.</p>I&rsquo;ll be the <a href="http://orcmid.com/construction/orcmid.htm">white-haired fellow</a> who still puts film in his camera.&nbsp; I&rsquo;ll also be trying out the free Wi-Fi with my Tablet PC.<div style="clear:both; padding-bottom: 0.25em;"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid 
       at <a href="http://orcmid.com/blog/2007/01/geek-dinner-with-jon-udell-thursday.asp">1/12/2007 01:20:26 PM</a></span>
	  
         <!-- 2004-05-10 -->
		<div class="blogComments">
			&nbsp;<br /><b><i>Comments:</i></b><!-- 2004-10-04 -->  
			
			<div class="blogComment">
				&nbsp;<br /><a name="116893134792256775"></a> 
				:(  Unfortunately this is at the same time as the Seattle podcasters meetup at Microsoft studios.  Hopefully Jon will still be around when the meetup ends<br />
				<div class="byline">
